'''Hilary Bertha Shuard''' [[Commander of the Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (14 November 1928{{spaced ndash}}24 December 1992) was an internationally known expert on mathematics in primary schools.

She was deputy principal of [[Homerton College, Cambridge]], [[England]] and was president of the [[Mathematical Association]] for 1985-1986.<ref>{{cite news|last=Reynolds|first=Peter|title=Obituary: Hilary Shuard|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/obituary-hilary-shuard-1476499.html|newspaper=The Independent|date=4 January 1993}}</ref>

