'''Silent protest''' is an organized effort where the participants stay quiet to demonstrate disapproval. It is used as a form of [[civil disobedience]] and [[nonviolent resistance]].<ref name=BBC>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/onthisday/hi/dates/stories/october/17/newsid_3535000/3535348.stm 1968: Black athletes make silent protest]</ref>
